pan class=title>   Hegegrolls Guide to succesful PoP-Hunting!</span><hr size=1> Firstoff!<br>
Plane of Power zones are MEGA-xp, but wont fill your pockets! Lots and lots of nice items drop there, alot level 61 and 62 spells, but nearly no vendor trash.<br>
Basically, in a PoP group you NEED:<br>
- a tank (better be level 52 or higher...52 is minimum from my experience).<br>
- a slower (a shaman, an enchanter, or, if you cannot find one of these, a beastlord <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
-a cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
-Crowd-Control: either a monk or a shadowknight to single pull...or an enchanter or a bard to mezz any adds<br>
<br>
The mobs in PoP hit incredibly hard. As a tank, always have virtue on you if you dare to tank these. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It is VITAL to slow any mob as soon as possible. A mob that is slowed 75 % by a lvl 51 shaman deals 75% less damage. You CANNOT kill even a single mob without it being slowed in PoP.<br>
<br>
Although the mobs in PoP hit hard, they have very few Hps compared to old world mobs. Take advantage of this by remaining spots in your group with  damage-dealing classes like e.g. magicians, wizards or rogues.  <br>
<br>
If you cannot find a group in PoP (even as a cleric i am /lfg for an hour or so sometimes...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START |I --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tired.gif ALT="|I"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), just start your own!<br>
<br>
/ all sham 51 62<br>
/ all ench 54 60<br>
/ all cleri  46 60<br>
<br>
If you see a shaman, enchanter or cleric just sitting in nexus, pok, or pot, or in a weirdo non-xp-zone like everfrost, west freeport or neriak, just sen him a tell and ask if he wants to join a pop-xp group. This is how i did it all the way from 50 to 62, and 1 out of 2 times im getting positive answers, even though these peeps were not /lfg. Sitting for 3 hours in pok or pot looking for group? Just start your own.<br>
<br>
Now where to hunt at what levels?<br>
<br>
46-52  Plane of Justice <br>
At the zoneout. You can pull level 46 mobs to the zoneout, if you are having trouble, you just click the zoneout door and leave. You WILL need this map to find your way around: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/pojustice1.gif">www.eqmaps.com/m3/pojustice1.gif</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
52-55 Plane of Nightmare/Plane of Innovation<br>
Kill the so-called graveyard-trash in these two zones. Plane of Innovation has better vendor loot and quest piecea for an amulett that gives you the ability to gate to plane of knowledge from any zone. AND nice magic items too.<br>
<br>
55-58 Plane of Nightmare/Plane of Disease<br>
Plane of Disease Castle Courtyard (ccy; left/right courtyard: lcy/rcy) are THE best xp in pop tier 1. Xping here took me from 50 to 60, though no one besides a cleric could probably hunt here effectively before he reaches 55. <br>
Plane of Nightmare: Stalker camp south of the zonein, or the much tougher Hobgoblins are very good xp and drop diamonds, raw dias and blue dias like mad! Also nice magic items drop in these camps.<br>
<br>
58-61 Plane of Disease<br>
Kill Castle Courtyard mobs. On your first few times you WILL need a lead to cy camps, and you better have invis up!<br>
Map: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/podisease1.gif">www.eqmaps.com/m3/podisease1.gif</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Thats it basically. Hope it helps! Keep in mind: The key to succesful hunting in any of these zones is a 52+ tank and someone who slows the mobs...and a cleric! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
