<br>
The second variety fight three ways: Hard, fast, and continuously.  For example: if one is pounding on you, forget any daydream of completing a cast.<br>
<br>
I hear that pet classes can solo a little, or those classes that can kite well.<br>
<br>
I've never yet heard of a melee soloist being successful there.<br>
<br>
In all likelihood, you're gonna have to bite the bullet and do some grouping.  Maybe Hege will invite you to be an additional damage dealer in some of his groups, now that Rgyle is of an age to join in.  Probably not as MT yet, but you could certainly /assist with the best!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:times new roman;font-size:medium;"> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eowenna.50megs.com/index.html" target="top">Eowenna Celerdain,</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Paladin of Light</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:times new roman;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> (and associates)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/bwingedalliance22062.showUserPublicProfile?gid=exodus77>exodus77</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/13/03 5:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/fwingedalliance22062frm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hegegrolls Guide to succesful PoP-Hunting!</span><hr size=1> I did a -ooc in pot and pok last night and asked some people, if and where a level 51 paladin could possibly solo for experience. Most People said the end of the solo line is 49 for melees, because of their lack of healing power and not enough damage output. The problem is simply: any mob that could give you the experience worth hunting it will take you down before you can kill it...<br>
I also asked how someone who can possibly be online for an hour or two only could level some, and got as an answer: duo with a shaman for an hour or two. <br>
Shaman + Tank :<br>
Everquests dream - team<br>
Shammy hastes Tank by 60% = 60 % more damage output. Shammy slows mob by 75 % = 75 % less damage intaken. Shammy BUFFS tanks strength, dexterity, stamina into EQ heaven - Shammy debuffs mobs melee stats until they hit like firebeetles. last, but not least, they throw in root and some mean and evil damage over time spells.<br>
Tank tanks. <br>
Most people said shammy and paladin both at 51 could fight at the plane of justice zoneout very easily and succesfully for very good xp. <br>
<br>
